---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-safetywing', text: 'Why SafetyWing for Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'limitations', text: 'Important Limitations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose SafetyWing', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Panama', href: '/countries/panama/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs Cigna', href: '/compare/safetywing-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Nomad Insurance', coverage: 'Travel medical', price: '$45-75/mo' },
  { plan: 'Remote Health', coverage: 'Health insurance', price: '$170-280/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing in Panama"
  description="Guide to SafetyWing insurance for digital nomads in Panama. Budget travel medical coverage for younger expats."
  headline="SafetyWing in Panama"
  subheadline="Budget-friendly travel medical insurance for digital nomads. Know the limitations before choosing."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/panama-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a SafetyWing Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Panama</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing offers affordable travel medical insurance designed for digital nomads and remote workers. For younger expats in Panama, it provides budget-friendly emergency coverage—but with significant limitations compared to comprehensive international health insurance.
  </p>
  <p>
    Panama's lack of mandatory insurance requirements means SafetyWing is legally acceptable. However, understand what you're getting (and not getting) before choosing this option.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45-75</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Nomad)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$250K</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Max coverage</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Travel</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Medical insurance</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Understand SafetyWing First"
    description="Know what's covered—and what isn't."
    buttonText="Learn More"
    buttonHref="/go/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-safetywing">Why SafetyWing for Panama</h2>

  <h3>Affordability</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's main advantage is price:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Nomad Insurance: ~$45-75/month depending on age</li>
    <li>No long-term commitment—month-to-month</li>
    <li>Easy signup process</li>
    <li>Covers 180+ countries including Panama</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Friendly</h3>
  <p>
    For the growing number of remote workers choosing Panama:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Designed for location-independent workers</li>
    <li>Covers travel between countries</li>
    <li>Includes home country visits (up to 30/90 days)</li>
    <li>No fixed address required</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Panama Context</h3>
  <p>
    Since Panama doesn't require health insurance for visas, SafetyWing is legally acceptable. However, this doesn't mean it's the best choice for everyone.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Best for Younger Nomads</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      SafetyWing works best for healthy digital nomads in their 20s-40s who want emergency coverage while keeping costs low. It's not designed for retirees or those with health conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="limitations">Important Limitations</h2>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">What SafetyWing Doesn't Cover</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
      <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Completely excluded</li>
      <li><strong>Routine/preventive care:</strong> Not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Not covered (except emergency complications)</li>
      <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Ongoing treatment excluded</li>
      <li><strong>Dental:</strong> Emergency only, limited benefit</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Coverage Limits</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Overall maximum:</strong> $250,000 per policy period</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> $250 per injury/illness</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital room:</strong> $250/day limit (may not cover full cost)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency room:</strong> $2,500 limit</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Not Real Health Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance. It covers emergencies and unexpected illnesses, not ongoing healthcare needs. If you have any health conditions or want comprehensive coverage, look at traditional international health insurance instead.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    The flagship product for digital nomads:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Travel medical coverage for emergencies</li>
    <li>~$45/month for age 18-39</li>
    <li>~$75/month for age 40-49</li>
    <li>Monthly subscription, cancel anytime</li>
    <li>Available up to age 69</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's actual health insurance product:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Comprehensive health coverage</li>
    <li>$170-280/month depending on age and options</li>
    <li>Covers more than Nomad Insurance</li>
    <li>Annual commitment</li>
    <li>Still has limitations vs. premium insurers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose SafetyWing in Panama</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">May Be Appropriate</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Young, healthy digital nomads</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious remote workers</li>
        <li>Those comfortable with limited coverage</li>
        <li>Short-term Panama stays</li>
        <li>People without pre-existing conditions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Not Appropriate</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Retirees (50+)</li>
        <li>Anyone with health conditions</li>
        <li>Those wanting comprehensive care</li>
        <li>Families with children</li>
        <li>Long-term Panama residents</li>
        <li>Anyone who may need ongoing care</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>For Panama Retirees</h3>
  <p>
    If you're a retiree considering Panama, SafetyWing is generally not recommended. Panama's retiree community benefits from comprehensive international health insurance that covers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (after waiting period)</li>
    <li>Chronic disease management</li>
    <li>Routine checkups and preventive care</li>
    <li>Higher coverage limits</li>
    <li>US coverage for visits home</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The Bottom Line</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing can work for young, healthy nomads who want emergency coverage at minimal cost. But it's not a substitute for real health insurance. If you're planning to stay in Panama long-term or have any health concerns, consider comprehensive international health insurance instead.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Panama Insurance Options"
    description="See comprehensive plans alongside budget options."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/go/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance. Review policy terms carefully before purchasing. Coverage limitations may result in significant out-of-pocket expenses for some medical situations.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
